# <span style="color:#ffb703">🔶 Part (ii): Active Loads</span>

## <span style="color:#00b4d8">📖 1. Introduction / Definition</span>

> [!info] Definition
> An **Active Load** is a circuit design technique where an active semiconductor device (like a MOSFET or BJT biased in the saturation/active region) is used instead of a passive resistor ($R_D$ or $R_C$) to act as the load for an amplifier.

---

## <span style="color:#00b4d8">🔑 2. Key Concepts & Need for Active Loads</span>

> [!danger] Drawback of Passive Resistors
> In a standard amplifier, voltage gain is directly proportional to the load resistance ($A_v = -g_m R_D$). To achieve very high gain, a ==massive resistor is needed==.

> [!warning] Area & Voltage Swing Issues
> - **Area Issue:** Large resistors consume too much space on a silicon chip, making them useless for VLSI ICs.
> - **Voltage Swing Issue:** A huge resistor creates a massive DC voltage drop, which can push the amplifier out of the saturation region and severely reduce the output voltage swing.

> [!success] Active Load Working
> By replacing the resistor with a transistor (e.g., a PMOS) acting as a constant current source, the circuit gains an **extremely high AC small-signal output resistance** ($r_o$). This provides tremendous voltage gain while keeping the physical size microscopic and the DC voltage drop minimal.

---

## <span style="color:#00b4d8">📐 3. Formula Representation</span>

> [!example] Gain Formulas
> **Gain with Passive Load:**
> $$A_v = -g_m R_D$$
> 
> ---
> **Gain with Active Load (Intrinsic Gain):**
> $$A_v = -g_m (r_{o1} \parallel r_{o2})$$
> 
> (Where $r_{o1}$ and $r_{o2}$ are the intrinsic output resistances of the amplifying and load transistors).

---

## <span style="color:#00b4d8">⚖️ 4. Advantages & Applications</span>

> [!success] Advantages
> - ==Drastically saves silicon chip area==.
> - Provides massive voltage gain (intrinsic gain typically 20 to 50).
> - Improves output voltage swing.

> [!tip] Applications
> Universally used in Op-Amp internal stages, Current Mirrors, and digital CMOS Inverters.

